Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-lake
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-lake
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Suggests: awscli
Description: PostgreSQL lakehouse extensions for PostgreSQL PGVERSION
 pg_lake integrates Iceberg tables and Parquet, CSV, and JSON data lake files
 with PostgreSQL. It provides transactional Iceberg access and delegates
 analytical execution to a bundled DuckDB engine through pgduck_server.
 .
 This package contains the pg_lake extension and its required component
 extensions, pgduck_server, and the private Avro and DuckDB runtime libraries.
 Before use, add pg_extension_base to shared_preload_libraries and run the
 versioned pgduck_server binary. Its first start may download DuckDB spatial.
